quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  42,32,And among His signs are the ships which sail like mountains upon the ocean
  42,33,"If He will, He calms the wind, so that they lie motionless upon its bosom:¹ surely there are signs in this for steadfast who render thanks"
  42,34,or He causes them to founder as punishment for their misdeeds.² Yet He forgives much
  42,35,Those who dispute Our revelations shall realize they have no escape
  42,36,That which you have been given is but the fleeting pleasure of this life. Better and more enduring is God‘s recompense to those who believe and put their trust in their Lord
  42,37,"who eschew grievous sins and lewd acts and, when angered, are willing to forgive"
  42,38,"who obey their Lord, attend to their prayers, and conduct their affairs by mutual counsel; who give in alms from what We gave them and"
  42,39,"when oppressed, seek to redress their wrongs"
  42,40,Let evil be requited with like evil. But he that forgives and seeks reconcilement shall be recompensed by God. He does not love the wrongdoers
  42,41,Those who seek to redress their wrongs incur no guilt
  42,42,But great is the guilt of those who oppress their fellow men and conduct themselves with wickedness and injustice in the land. Woeful punishment awaits them
  42,43,To endure with fortitude and to forgive is a duty incumbent on all
  42,44,"He whom God confounds has no protector after him. And you shall see the wrongdoers when they behold the scourge, say: ‘Is there no way back?‘"